---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import MarketingNav from '../components/MarketingNav.astro';
import MarketingSiteFooter from '../components/MarketingSiteFooter.astro';

const title = 'Legal & privacy';
const description =
  'Privacy policy and terms of use for Surgical eLogbook: operative training logbook with no patient identifiable data.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-white font-sans text-slate-900">
    <MarketingNav current="legal" />

    <div class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-clinical-50 via-white to-surface-muted">
      <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-24 top-0 h-72 w-72 rounded-full bg-clinical-100/60 blur-3xl"></div>
      <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -left-16 bottom-0 h-64 w-64 rounded-full bg-slate-200/40 blur-3xl"></div>
      <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-12 pt-10 sm:px-6 sm:pb-16 sm:pt-14">
        <p class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-clinical-600">Legal centre</p>
        <h1 class="mt-2 max-w-2xl text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
          Privacy & terms in one place
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
          How we handle your account and training data, and the rules that apply when you use Surgical eLogbook.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-16 pt-10 sm:px-6 sm:pt-12">
      <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,14rem)_minmax(0,1fr)] lg:gap-12 xl:gap-16">
        <aside class="mb-10 hidden lg:block">
          <nav class="sticky top-24 space-y-1 text-sm" aria-label="On this page">
            <p class="mb-2 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400">On this page</p>
            <a href="#privacy-policy" class="block rounded-lg px-3 py-2 font-medium text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100">
              Privacy policy
            </a>
            <a href="#terms-of-use" class="block rounded-lg px-3 py-2 font-medium text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100">
              Terms of use
            </a>
            <a href="#faq" class="block rounded-lg px-3 py-2 font-medium text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100">FAQ</a>
          </nav>
        </aside>

        <div class="min-w-0 space-y-16">
          <section id="privacy-policy" class="scroll-mt-28 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/90 bg-white p-6 shadow-card sm:p-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Privacy policy</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString(undefined, { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>

            <div class="prose prose-slate prose-headings:scroll-mt-28 mt-8 max-w-none prose-p:text-slate-700 prose-li:text-slate-700 prose-strong:text-slate-900">
              <h3>What we collect</h3>
              <p>
                Surgical eLogbook stores your <strong>account email</strong>, <strong>grade</strong>,{' '}
                <strong>preferences</strong> (for example name title, full name, GMC number, default trust, specialty,
                tags, and form defaults), <strong>saved consultants</strong> (firstname, surname, GMC for reuse on
                forms), and each <strong>case entry</strong> you save (date, specialty, trust or hospital name from the
                official list, procedure tags, CEPOD category, consultant details, your role, and optional notes).
              </p>
              <h3>What we do not want</h3>
              <p>
                You must <strong>not</strong> enter patient identifiable information anywhere in the app, including in
                notes. That means no patient names, NHS numbers, hospital numbers, dates of birth, addresses, phone
                numbers, or anything else that could identify an individual patient.
              </p>
              <h3>PDF reports</h3>
              <p>
                Training PDFs are <strong>generated in your browser</strong> on your device. They are not uploaded to or
                stored on our servers as part of that process.
              </p>
              <h3>Analytics</h3>
              <p>
                This product does <strong>not</strong> include third party advertising or analytics scripts by default.
                If your deployment adds analytics, that should be disclosed separately by whoever operates the instance.
              </p>
              <h3>Your controls</h3>
              <p>
                From the app you can <strong>export</strong> your cases (for example CSV or JSON, depending on what the app
                offers) and <strong>delete your account</strong>. Account deletion is intended to remove your profile and
                logbook data from the application database; removing the underlying authentication account may depend on
                your operator’s configuration (see deployment documentation).
              </p>
              <h3>Contact</h3>
              <p>
                For questions about this policy or product messaging:{' '}
                <a href="mailto:surgicalelogbook@proton.me" class="font-semibold text-clinical-700 hover:underline">
                  surgicalelogbook@proton.me
                </a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="terms-of-use" class="scroll-mt-28 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/90 bg-white p-6 shadow-card sm:p-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Terms of use</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString(undefined, { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>

            <div class="prose prose-slate prose-headings:scroll-mt-28 mt-8 max-w-none prose-p:text-slate-700 prose-li:text-slate-700 prose-strong:text-slate-900">
              <h3>Purpose</h3>
              <p>
                Surgical eLogbook is an <strong>educational and training logbook</strong>. It is not an official medical
                record, legal record of care, or a mandated clinical system. Your deanery, employer, trust, or regulator may
                require additional evidence, signatures, or approved systems.
              </p>
              <h3>Your responsibilities</h3>
              <p>
                You are responsible for the accuracy and lawfulness of what you enter. You must not enter
                patient identifiable information. Do not rely on this app as the sole record where another system is
                required by policy or law.
              </p>
              <h3>Software disclaimer</h3>
              <p>
                The software is provided <strong>“as is”</strong>, without warranties of any kind to the extent permitted
                by law. To the extent permitted by law, operators and contributors are not liable for loss arising from use
                or inability to use the service.
              </p>
              <h3>Changes</h3>
              <p>
                We may update these terms or the privacy policy from time to time. Continued use of the app after changes
                are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated documents where applicable law allows.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-28">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Common questions</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Quick answers: full detail is in the sections above.</p>
            <dl class="mt-6 space-y-3">
              <details class="group rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm open:bg-slate-50/80">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer list-none px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900 marker:hidden [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
                  <span class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2">
                    Where is my data stored?
                    <span class="text-slate-400 transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
                  </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="border-t border-slate-100 px-4 py-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                  Case rows and your profile live in the database used by your deployment (for example Supabase). PDFs you
                  generate stay on your device unless you choose to share them yourself.
                </div>
              </details>
              <details class="group rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm open:bg-slate-50/80">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer list-none px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900 marker:hidden [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
                  <span class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2">
                    Can I use notes for reflective practice?
                    <span class="text-slate-400 transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
                  </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="border-t border-slate-100 px-4 py-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                  Yes. Reflective notes are fine as long as they contain <strong>no patient identifiable information</strong>.
                </div>
              </details>
              <details class="group rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm open:bg-slate-50/80">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer list-none px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900 marker:hidden [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
                  <span class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2">
                    Is this approved by the GMC or my deanery?
                    <span class="text-slate-400 transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
                  </span>
                </summary>
                <div class="border-t border-slate-100 px-4 py-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                  The app is a tool to help you keep a structured log. Formal approval for portfolio or ARCP submission is
                  between you and your local educators. Always follow their guidance.
                </div>
              </details>
            </dl>
          </section>

          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-clinical-600 to-clinical-800 px-6 py-10 text-center text-white shadow-card sm:px-10">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-white/80">Still unsure?</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-bold">We’re happy to hear from trainees and trainers.</p>
            <a
              href="mailto:surgicalelogbook@proton.me"
              class="mt-6 inline-flex rounded-xl bg-white px-6 py-3 text-sm font-bold text-clinical-800 shadow-sm transition hover:bg-clinical-50"
            >
              surgicalelogbook@proton.me
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <MarketingSiteFooter hideSecondaryNav={true} />
  </div>
</Layout>
